<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>Law Career Path</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="stream-detail.css">
</head>
<body>
  <header class="stream-hero">
    <span>Justice and Policy Stream</span>
    <h1>Law Career Path</h1>
    <p>Law is the study of justice, rights, rules, society, contracts, courts, governance, and legal problem-solving. It suits students who like reading, reasoning, debate, writing, and public issues.</p>
  </header>
  <main class="stream-shell">
    <section class="quick-grid">
      <div class="quick-card"><strong>Main Subjects</strong>Legal reasoning, English, GK, logic, social science</div>
      <div class="quick-card"><strong>Common Exams</strong>CLAT, AILET, LSAT India, CUET, university tests</div>
      <div class="quick-card"><strong>Best For</strong>Debate, reading, reasoning, justice, policy</div>
    </section>
    <h2 class="section-title">Popular Law Fields</h2>
    <section class="path-grid">
      <div class="path-card active"><h3>Criminal Law</h3><p>Work with offences, trials, evidence, rights, and court practice.</p></div>
      <div class="path-card"><h3>Corporate Law</h3><p>Handle contracts, companies, compliance, mergers, and business legal work.</p></div>
      <div class="path-card"><h3>Civil Law</h3><p>Resolve property, family, consumer, and private disputes.</p></div>
      <div class="path-card"><h3>Public Policy</h3><p>Work with governance, law-making, research, and social impact.</p></div>
    </section>
    <section class="tabs">
      <button class="tab-btn active" data-target="courses">Courses</button>
      <button class="tab-btn" data-target="exams">Entrance Exams</button>
      <button class="tab-btn" data-target="careers">Careers</button>
      <button class="tab-btn" data-target="skills">Skills</button>
    </section>
    <section class="detail-panel">
      <div id="courses" class="tab-panel active"><h2>Courses You Can Choose</h2><ul><li>BA LLB, BBA LLB, B.Com LLB after 12th.</li><li>LLB after graduation.</li><li>Political Science, Public Administration, Criminology, or Policy courses.</li></ul></div>
      <div id="exams" class="tab-panel"><h2>Entrance Exams</h2><ul><li>CLAT for National Law Universities.</li><li>AILET for NLU Delhi.</li><li>LSAT India, CUET, and state or university law entrance exams.</li></ul></div>
      <div id="careers" class="tab-panel"><h2>Career Options</h2><ul><li>Lawyer, Legal Advisor, Judge after required exams and experience.</li><li>Corporate Counsel, Legal Analyst, Compliance Officer.</li><li>Civil Services, Policy Analyst, Legal Journalist, Professor.</li></ul></div>
      <div id="skills" class="tab-panel"><h2>Skills To Build</h2><ul><li>Reading speed, legal reasoning, writing, and debate.</li><li>Current affairs, constitution basics, and analytical thinking.</li><li>Confidence for internships, moot courts, and client communication.</li></ul></div>
    </section>
    <section class="planner"><h2>Student Checklist</h2><label><input type="checkbox"> Read current affairs daily.</label><label><input type="checkbox"> Practice logical and legal reasoning questions.</label><label><input type="checkbox"> Compare BA LLB, BBA LLB, and LLB routes.</label></section>
    <div class="back-row"><a class="action-link" href="career.jsp">Back to Career Streams</a></div>
  </main>
  <script src="stream-detail.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
